not been using our natural forest resources wisely. Over half the world&#8217;s forest are already gone and if we continue &#8211; &nbsp;business as usual &#8211; &nbsp;and do nothing about this, then forest loss is predicted to reach an incredible 232 million hectares. Here are five [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Deforestation","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/deforestation/","slug":"deforestation"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Orangutan","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/orangutan/","slug":"orangutan"},{"name":"Sumatra","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/sumatra/","slug":"sumatra"},{"name":"tiger","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/tiger/","slug":"tiger"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"},{"name":"Sustainable Consumption","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/sustainable-consumption/","slug":"sustainable-consumption"},{"name":"Wildlife","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/wildlife/","slug":"wildlife"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4-300x225.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4.jpg 1024w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoxNjQ0","title":"THE HEAT IS ON","uri":"the-heat-is-on/","slug":"the-heat-is-on","date":"2016-04-22T06:16:11","content":"<p>1.5 degrees is the magic number Remember this number: 1.5 degrees. That&#8217;s the upper limit for global warming that our governments will try to stay under, as agreed at the global climate negotiations in Paris last year. Everything all of us do from this point on will be measured against it. Getting this agreement was [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"1.5 degrees","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/1-5-degrees/","slug":"1-5-degrees"},{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Paris Agreement","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/paris-agreement/","slug":"paris-agreement"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Ocean","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/ocean/","slug":"ocean"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/GER0465-sm.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/GER0465-sm-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/GER0465-sm.jpg 1000w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoxNTI3","title":"A Hazy Issue: What can we as individuals do to help?","uri":"hazy-issue-can-individuals-help/","slug":"hazy-issue-can-individuals-help","date":"2016-03-07T07:24:02","content":"<p>WHAT CAN WE AS INDIVIDUALS DO TO HELP? by Katie Roberts, Expat Living Magazine While the political and corporate response to last year’s terrible haze pollution has been less than overwhelming, its causes and the consequences for people across Southeast Asia are clear. In view of the haze predicted to return this month, we took [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"#XtheHaze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/xthehaze/","slug":"xthehaze"},{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Earth Hour","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/earth-hour/","slug":"earth-hour"},{"name":"Orangutan","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/orangutan/","slug":"orangutan"},{"name":"Palm Oil","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/palm-oil/","slug":"palm-oil"},{"name":"Transboundary Haze Pollution Act","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/transboundary-haze-pollution-act/","slug":"transboundary-haze-pollution-act"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4.jpg","altText":null,"srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4-300x225.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/hazeblog4.jpg 1024w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDozNTQ=","title":"COP21: Hits &#038; Misses","uri":"cop21-hits-misses-2/","slug":"cop21-hits-misses-2","date":"2015-12-16T20:58:35","content":"<p>1. Temperatures to be kept well below 2 degrees, and aiming for a 1.5 degree goal [stag_columns][stag_one_half]What we like Scientists have told us that 1.5 degrees is the critical threshold before we witness catastrophic changes to our climate (think mass migrations for hundreds of millions of people!). By recognising the 1.5 degree goal, governments are [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"COP21","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cop21/","slug":"cop21"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Paris","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/paris/","slug":"paris"},{"name":"UNFCCC","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/unfccc/","slug":"unfccc"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-300x113.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-768x288.jpg 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change-1024x384.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/adapting-to-climate-change.jpg 1600w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyOTY=","title":"Forests: A hot topic at COP21","uri":"forests-a-hot-topic-at-cop21/","slug":"forests-a-hot-topic-at-cop21","date":"2015-12-08T16:37:42","content":"<p>At this year’s UN climate talks in Paris, the spotlight finally shone on an often understated, under-appreciated solution for combating climate change – protecting our forests. Unbeknown to most, deforestation is the second-largest emitter of global CO2 emissions, accounting for nearly 11% of global CO2 emissions. That’s more than the entire transport sector, and only [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"COP21","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cop21/","slug":"cop21"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-300x97.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-768x248.jpg 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1-1024x331.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cop21-forest1.jpg 1548w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyNjc=","title":"1 in 6 species at risk of extinction","uri":"1-in-6-species-at-risk-of-extinction/","slug":"1-in-6-species-at-risk-of-extinction","date":"2015-12-04T12:27:50","content":"<p>Move or adapt To survive, plants, animals and birds confronted with climate change have two options: Option one &#8211; ADAPT:  With the speed of climate change we are experiencing already, it’s often not possible for a species to adapt quickly enough to keep up with its changing environment. Option two &#8211; MOVE:  With the amount of habitat [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Orangutan","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/orangutan/","slug":"orangutan"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Endangered Species","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/endangered-species/","slug":"endangered-species"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Wildlife","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/wildlife/","slug":"wildlife"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/orangutan.jpg","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/orangutan-300x97.jpg 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/orangutan-768x248.jpg 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/orangutan-1024x331.jpg 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/orangutan.jpg 1548w"}},{"id":"cG9zdDoyNDE=","title":"5 things to learn from the haze about changing climate change","uri":"5-things-to-learn-from-the-haze-about-changing-climate-change/","slug":"5-things-to-learn-from-the-haze-about-changing-climate-change","date":"2015-11-07T16:20:35","content":"<p>If you have seen the news from Southeast Asia recently, you would know the haze is back again, impacting health, lives and livelihoods of thousands. Caused mainly by illegal slash and burn practices to clear land to meet the growing demand for pulp, paper and palm oil, the haze is widely regarded as an (almost) [&hellip;]</p>\n","author":{"name":"Louise Wood","slug":"louise-wood","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/08b72de95886dc800efe0347f324f87a?s=100&d=mm&r=g"}},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"#XtheHaze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/xthehaze/","slug":"xthehaze"},{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Forest","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/forest/","slug":"forest"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/haze/","slug":"haze"},{"name":"Palm Oil","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/palm-oil/","slug":"palm-oil"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"Haze","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/haze/","slug":"haze"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]},"featuredImage":{"sourceUrl":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/RiauProject.png","altText":"","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/RiauProject-300x117.png 300w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/RiauProject-768x298.png 768w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/RiauProject-1024x398.png 1024w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/RiauProject.png 1591w"}}]}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"cG9zdF90YWc6Ng==","databaseId":6,"slug":"climate-change"}}}